The paper focuses on Quality Diversity (QD) algorithms, which are commonly used in robotics and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.AI and cs.RO are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of surprise as a diversity measure, which falls under the category of machine learning and can be classified under cs.LG and cs.NE. Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed algorithms in a robot navigation task, which falls under the category of control systems and can be classified under cs.SY.
